Vice President Biden released a statement on August 13, 2009, regarding the launch of a $2.3 billion recovery act green manufacturer tax credit program. He emphasized the importance of not just rescuing the economy, but also rebuilding it better, starting with providing American manufacturers with resources to produce clean, green energy technology. The program aims to increase manufacturing of green energy materials in the country and create thousands of new jobs. The recovery will be fueled by the incentives offered to businesses through the Recovery Act, which will be the engine of the future economy.